        increase to \raisebox{-0.5ex}\textasciitilde15 per cent. We find
        comparable results from more detailed simulations of the Zwicky
        Transient Facility surveys. Using the recovery efficiencies from
        these detailed simulations, we investigate the number of young
        Type Ia supernovae expected to be discovered assuming some
        fraction of the population comes from scenarios producing an
        excess at early times. Comparing the results of our simulations
        to observations, we find that the intrinsic fraction of Type Ia
        supernovae with early flux excesses is $\sim 28^{+13}_{-11}{{\
