        process that is distinct from the one that generates the
        UV/optical/near-infrared emission. No ultra-high-energy gamma-
        rays and no neutrino candidates consistent with the source were
        found in follow-up searches. These observations support the
        hypothesis that GW170817 was produced by the merger of two
        neutron stars in NGC 4993 followed by a short gamma-ray burst
        (GRB 170817A) and a kilonova/macronova powered by the
        radioactive decay of r-process nuclei synthesized in the ejecta.
